Abstract Photography, focuses on shapes, colors, and patterns rather than recognizable subjects
Action Photography, captures dynamic movement and high-energy moments
Analogue Photography, classic film grain and vintage tones
Architectural Photography, emphasizes building design, geometry, and structural perspective
Artistic Photography, creative composition and expressive visual storytelling
Astrophotography, captures stars, planets, and celestial phenomena
B&W Photography, dramatic contrast and timeless monochrome tones
Beauty Photography, flawless skin and elegant portrait lighting
Boudoir Photography, intimate and sensual portrait style with soft lighting
Candid Photography, spontaneous and natural moments without posing
Cinematic Photography, film-like composition with dramatic lighting and wide aspect ratio
Conceptual Photography, staged scenes that convey abstract ideas or narratives
Documentary Photography, authentic and real-life storytelling
Double Exposure Photography, two superimposed images blended for surreal layered effect
Dreamy Haze Photography, soft focus and ethereal lighting effects
Drone Photography, elevated aerial perspective capturing landscapes and patterns from above
Editorial Photography, story-driven images for magazines with styled subjects and settings
Erotic Photography, sensual and intimate visual expression
Event Photography, captures moments and atmosphere at gatherings and celebrations
Fine Art Photography, artistic vision and creative expression prioritized over documentation
Food Photography, appetizing close-ups with styled plating and controlled lighting
Glamour Photography, stylish poses and luxurious atmosphere
Glitch Style Photography, digital distortion and experimental effects
HDR Photography, high dynamic range combining multiple exposures for vivid detail in all tones
High Fashion Photography, bold styling and dramatic editorial looks
Infrared Photography, captures invisible spectrum for surreal glowing foliage and dark skies
Instant Photography, Polaroid-like snapshots with retro charm
Landscape Photography, sweeping natural vistas with dramatic skies and deep depth of field
Large Format Photography, ultra-high resolution and fine detail
Lifestyle Photography, relaxed and authentic everyday scenes
Light Painting Photography, long exposure with moving light sources for luminous trails
Long Exposure Photography, motion blur and light trails for creative effects
Macro Photography, extreme close-ups revealing tiny details
Micro Photography, highly magnified images of microscopic subjects
Minimalist Photography, sparse composition with clean lines and negative space
Modernist Photography, geometric forms and experimental composition
Night Photography, captures low-light scenes with moody shadows and artificial illumination
Paparazzi Photography, candid celebrity moments and spontaneous captures
Pictorialist Photography, soft focus and painterly effects for artistic mood
Pinhole Photography, dreamy vignettes and unique perspective
Polaroid Photography, instant prints with nostalgic color shifts
Portrait Photography, focused on facial features and expression with shallow depth of field
Product Photography, clean and precise shots showcasing objects with controlled studio lighting
Sports Photography, freezes high-speed athletic action with sharp focus and dynamic framing
Street Fashion Photography, urban settings and candid style portraits
Surrealist Photography, dreamlike and imaginative visual concepts
Tilt-Shift Photography, selective focus creating miniature-model effect on real scenes
Underwater Photography, submerged scenes with aquatic colors and light refraction
Vignette Photography, darkened edges for focused and moody composition
Vintage Photography, aged tones and film artifacts evoking past decades
Wildlife Photography, captures animals in natural habitats with telephoto detail
X-Ray Photography, revealing internal structures with translucent effects
